        \n                            \u003cp\u003eThe Amazon Fire Max 11 features a high-resolution LCD, 14 hours of battery life, and 4GB of RAM paired with Amazon\u0026#39;s ecosystem and support.Â \u003c/p\u003e\n            \n            \n            \n\n            \n            \n            \n                            \n            \n            \n            \n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026#39;ve been looking for an \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-cheap-android-tablets/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eaffordable tablet\u003c/a\u003e with a good screen, lots of power, and great battery life, the \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/amazon-fire-max-11-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAmazon Fire Max 11\u003c/a\u003e is going to be a good choice. This is going to be the best Amazon tablet you can buy, and while we did have some hesitations recommending it at its original retail price of $230, we think this becomes a no-brainer since it\u0026#39;s now down to the lowest price we\u0026#39;ve seen at just $140. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/amazon-prime-day-2025/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"Amazon Prime Day 2025 promotional banner from Android Police\" src=\"https://static0.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/img_0103.png\"/\u003e\n \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-amazon-fire-max-11\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Amazon Fire Max 11?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\u003cp\u003eThe real star of the show here is going to be the tablet\u0026#39;s beautiful large display that comes in at 11 inches and also features a resolution of 2000 x 1200. In addition, you also get a powerful octa-core processor that\u0026#39;s paired with 4GB of RAM and 64GB of internal storage. Of course, you can always expand the storage using a microSD card. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eAs far as construction goes, you\u0026#39;re getting excellent durability here with a tablet that can handle being dumped or dropped. Amazon is quite proud of this, declaring that the Fire Max 11 is three times as durable as the Apple iPad. Of course, your results may vary, and \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-amazon-fire-max-11-cases/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ewe always recommend grabbing a case\u003c/a\u003e if you think it might be in some rough situations. \u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"ca02-4436-8d868f2c14c5\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t\n\t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/amazon-fire-max-11-review/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/amazon-fire-max-11-07.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                          